  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 04:11 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Liquidation Detector + Indicator Bug Status\n\n**Task:** Build liquidation cascade detector (new alpha data source) and investigate the indicator logging bug.\n\n**Built: intelligence/liquidation-detector.py**\n- Tracks OI changes + price movement on BTC, ETH, SOL via HL API\n- Detects long/short liquidation events and cascades\n- Translates to PM signal: long cascade = bearish (block YES), short cascade = bullish (boost YES)\n- Saves to `intelligence/liq-signals.json` (consumed by bot) + `liq-history.jsonl` (analytics)\n- Added to cron: runs every 5 minutes\n- First run captured baseline; second run confirmed comparison logic works\n- Current market: BTC $67,591, no liquidation events, very flat funding (0.0003%)\n\n**Investigated: Indicator Logging Bug**\n- Root cause IDENTIFIED: The `\ud83d\udccb Indicators captured` debug line EXISTS in code (line 614) but has NOT been tested yet\n- Current bot instance started 22:43 UTC Mar 30 \u2014 zero trades since (off-hours all night)\n- The indicator dict IS populated at `_last_indicators` (line 556-563)\n- The dict IS passed to `_check_outcome` as `trade_indicators` (line 612)\n- `_check_outcome` passes it to `log_trade_outcome` which calls `outcome_entry.update(indicators)` (line 196-197)\n- **Theory:** The code path looks correct. The bug may have been in a PREVIOUS version (pre-22:43 restart). Need to wait for first V4.1 trade at 11h UTC to confirm.\n- If indicators still missing after 11h trade \u2192 the dict is empty at capture time (race condition between indicator calc and trade execution in async loop)\n\n**Market snapshot at 04:13 UTC:**\n- BTC: $67,591 | Funding: +0.0003% | OI: $1.82B\n- ETH: $2,065 | Funding: +0.0013% | OI: $1.18B  \n- SOL: $83.54 | Funding: +0.0008% | OI: $305M\n- Regime: MIXED (score 3/6), dominant UP, ATR 1.43%\n- Copy signal: bearish@80% (37/50 sells, 45/50 down tokens)\n- No extreme funding anywhere \u2014 very flat market\n\n**My thinking:** The liquidation detector fills a real gap. Our regime filter catches slow trends but MISSES sudden liquidation cascades that cause 1-3% moves in minutes. Those cascades are exactly when our contrarian YES strategy gets destroyed (we buy YES, then longs get liquidated and price dumps further). The detector will give us a real-time signal to BLOCK trades during cascades.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Liquidation detector is LIVE on cron. Will collect data this week.\n- V5 integration: wire `liq-signals.json` into bot's conviction scoring (pm_adjustment field)\n- Indicator bug: WAIT until 11h trade to confirm fixed. If still broken \u2192 add explicit debug print of dict contents at line 612.\n- Next P4 work: analyze first 24h of liquidation data for signal quality.\n\n**Next P4:** Review liquidation detector output quality after 24h of collection. Correlate detected events with PM trade outcomes.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 04:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] V5 Strategy Optimization: min_bias Filter + H",
